				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R_0$$\end{document}R0), among other important epidemic course parameters. Moreover, such models can show how different public health interventions (e.g. vaccination, limited social contacts, lockdown) may affect the outcome of the epidemic.

