				\begin{document}$$\gamma$$\end{document}γ is the removal rate (the inverse of the removal period in days). When some of these three parameters are considered fixed, they do not, in general, fit the observed course of the current epidemic. For example, the social distancing measures or even the lockdown damp the transmission rate down by reducing the daily contacts one person regularly has; or the improvement and gained experience of the health care system pull the removal rate up by lowering the recovery period or the death rate. Making these two parameters, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
