				\begin{document}$$R_0$$\end{document}R0) is 3.434 with a 95% credible interval of (3.312–3.535) and varies between 3.250 and 4.165. The distribution of the basic reproduction number is depicted in Fig. 9a. The temporal evolution of the effective reproduction number is represented in Fig. 9b. The imposition of the lockdown and social distancing measures were effective in pulling the reproduction number down to a value below the epidemic control of one. Nevertheless, easing those measures implied a significant increase on the infection transmission in early May. Still, the level that was reached kept the disease’s spread under control and additional restrictions made it possible to bring it to levels close to the threshold, although the end of the epidemic cannot be anticipated yet.Figure 9
